    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring frequently, until you're left with a sandy paste</p><p>Whisk in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Marmite</strong>, <strong>onion marmalade </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>onion</strong> <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
